author: Megan Ellis
title: Plane hits...a kangaroo?
text:
Need a flight? We'll scan dozens of airlines and get you the best fare in seconds! Plane hits...a kangaroo? Fri, 31 Jul 2015 3:55 PM Share Your Email A file image of a kangaroo. Credit: sxc.hu 
There are many reasons a flight can get cancelled- but this is the first time we've heard of a cancellation due to a plane hitting a kangaroo. 
This is what happened to a Melbourne-bound passenger plane in Victoria. 
Rex Airlines flight ZL3653 was cancelled after the plane's right propeller hit a kangaroo during takeoff, damaging the propeller, the Herald Sun reported. 
The incident occurred at the Mildura Airport at 6.30am on Thursday. 
This is the first time a plane has hit a kangaroo in six years at the airport, the Sunraysia Daily reported. 
Whether or not the animal survived is unclear. Related Articles
